                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/304.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-30T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 27, 11 a.m. The Department will let the British and French warships
                    arrive at Mexican ports before passing finally upon the question of the
                    advisability of sending an American warship.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
